    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-30T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-30T12:00:00-05:00" n="577"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/652</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-30T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>720. War Trade Board from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_TAE1"
                        >Taylor</persName>:</p>
                <p>No. 1133. Replying your 915.<note n="1" xml:id="d577fn1">Not printed; see War
                        Trade Board’s telegram No. 881, Department’s No. 289, July 18, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1515">p. 1515</ref>.</note> I
                    advise you to trade exports against tin and quinine and anything else you want.
                    My last cable expresses my feeling that a general agreement will be long
                    delayed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
